g%2C%20a%20native%20Midwesterner%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20to%20the%20Phoenix%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoudenberg%2C%2060%2C%20still%20hasn't%20gotten%20used%20to%20the%20state's%20blistering%20summers.%20Once%20a%20resident%20of%20the%20Great%20Lakes%20area%2C%20she%20missed%20going%20to%20the%20beach%20and%20watching%20the%20leaves%20change%20colors%20in%20the%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20never%20been%20happy%20with%20the%20heat%2C%26quot%3B%20Woudenberg%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20fall%2C%20she%20bought%20a%20cabin%20near%20Baldwin%2C%20Michigan%2C%20a%20city%20about%2085%20miles%20north%20of%20Grand%20Rapids%2C%20where%20she%20planned%20to%20spend%20the%20warmer%20months%20instead%20of%20hunkering%20down%20indoors%20in%20air%20conditioning%20and%20waiting%20for%20the%20Arizona%20heat%20to%20subside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoudenberg%20said%20splitting%20time%20between%20Arizona%20and%20Michigan%20allows%20her%20to%20enjoy%20the%20positives%20of%20both%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20very%20outdoorsy%20%E2%80%94%20I%20love%20to%20garden%2C%20and%20in%20Arizona%2C%20you%20do%20not%20garden%20in%20the%20summer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20garden%20a%20lot%20in%20Arizona%20in%20the%20wintertime%2C%20so%20now%20I%20get%20the%20best%20of%20both%20worlds.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoudenberg%20participates%20in%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20popular%20%26quot%3Bsnowbird%26quot%3B%20trend%2C%20in%20which%20cold-averse%20people%20fly%20south%20for%20the%20winter.%20%26quot%3BSweat%20birds%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%26quot%3Bfire%20birds%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20Woudenberg%20prefers%20%E2%80%94%20ditch%20the%20heat%20and%20opt%20for%20a%20cooler%20experience%20in%20the%20summer%20by%20relocating%20north.%20It%20offers%20outdoorsy%20people%20more%20opportunities%20to%20do%20the%20activities%20they%20love%20throughout%20the%20year%20without%20worrying%20about%2C%20say%2C%20sweating%20through%20their%20favorite%20shirt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20Midwesterner%20living%20in%20Arizona%20returns%20North%20to%20continue%20her%20life%20outdoors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWoudenberg%20still%20has%20family%20in%20Michigan.%20That%20was%20a%20big%20draw%20for%20her%20deciding%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20up%20North%2C%20but%20the%20climate%20also%20played%20a%20major%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoudenberg%20enjoys%20outdoor%20activities%20like%20hiking%2C%20biking%2C%20and%20boating%2C%20but%20the%20weather%20in%20Arizona%20denies%20her%20those%20pleasures%20during%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22496%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20posing%20in%20front%20of%20yellow%20flowers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ee36022dfb7800199fe5a8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWoudenberg%20is%20originally%20from%20the%20Midwest%20and%20missed%20spending%20time%20there.%3Cp%3ECindy%20Woudenberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20not%20out%20by%204%20a.m.%20or%205%20a.m.%2C%20it's%20just%20too%20hot%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sometimes%20even%20then%20it's%20hot%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArizona%20has%20had%20a%20blazingly%20hot%20summer%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F31%2Fus%2Fphoenix-heat-july.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etemperatures%20hitting%20at%20least%20110%20degrees%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%2031%20days%20straight%20during%20June%20and%20July.%20Michigan's%20summer%20temperatures%20average%20highs%20in%20the%2070s%20and%20let%20Woudenberg%20carry%20on%20with%20her%20favorite%20outdoor%20activities.%20Woudenberg%20said%20her%20life%20in%20Michigan%20mirrors%20her%20life%20in%20Arizona%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20she's%20normally%20doing%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20during%20different%20times%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20really%20isn't%20that%20much%20difference%20as%20far%20as%20outdoor%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20opposite%20seasons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHiking%20in%20Arizona%20is%20great%20when%20the%20weather%20is%20tame%2C%20Woudenberg%20said%2C%20and%20when%20it's%20warm%20enough%2C%20the%20National%20Forest%20trails%20in%20Michigan%20are%20beautiful.%20Woudenberg%20said%20that%20Arizona%20has%20an%20avid%20boating%20community%2C%20but%20the%20heat%20dictates%20when%20you%20can%20get%20out%20on%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoating%20in%20the%20summer%20is%20still%20miserable%20unless%20you're%20swimming%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20do%20boat%2C%20but%20mostly%20they're%20boating%20in%20the%20spring%2C%20winter%2C%20fall.%20In%20Michigan%2C%20it's%20the%20opposite.%20In%20Michigan%20you're%20boating%20until%20everything%20freezes%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoudenberg%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20prices%20of%20homes%20inland%20are%20not%20as%20expensive%20as%20lakeshore%20homes.%20Her%20three-bedroom%20cabin%20is%20about%2030%20minutes%20from%20Lake%20Michigan.%20The%20median%20home-sale%20price%20in%20Baldwin%2C%20Michigan%2C%20is%20%24114%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20Redfin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20Woudenberg's%20first%20summer%20owning%20a%20second%20home%20in%20Michigan.%20She%20plans%20on%20spending%20about%20five%20months%20(June%20through%20October)%20up%20North%2C%20although%20the%20foliage%20in%20the%20fall%20may%20have%20her%20extend%20her%20time%20to%20November.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20spring%20is%20spectacular%20down%20in%20Arizona%20for%20weather%20because%20it'll%20be%2070%20or%2080%20degrees%20and%20sunny%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20colors%20in%20Michigan%20are%20just%20amazing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20Florida%20couple%20leaves%20their%20destination%20city%20for%20Idaho%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGalia%20and%20Mike%20Pennekamp%20spend%20about%2075%25%20of%20their%20time%20in%20Mia