r-forward-deployment-not-about-land-grab%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eforward%20deployment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20troops.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIssuing%20the%20statement%20about%20the%20protest%2C%20MEA%E2%80%99s%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20reject%20these%20claims%20as%20they%20have%20no%20basis.%20Such%20steps%20by%20the%20Chinese%20side%20only%20complicate%20the%20resolution%20of%20the%20boundary%20question.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20have%20today%20lodged%20a%20strong%20protest%20through%20diplomatic%20channels%20with%20the%20Chinese%20side%20on%20the%20so-called%202023%20%E2%80%98standard%20map%E2%80%99%20of%20China%20that%20lays%20claim%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20territory%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi.%20He%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20reject%20these%20claims%20as%20they%20have%20no%20basis.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20most%20recent%20action%20came%20just%20a%20few%20days%20after%20a%20recent%20interaction%20between%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20during%20the%20BRICS%20summit.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edisparate%20accounts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20the%20two%20sides%20about%20the%20conversation%20concerning%20the%20border%20stand-off%20underscored%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20common%20understanding%20on%20de-escalation%20and%20disengagement%20on%20all%20the%20remaining%20friction%20points.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPresident%20Xi%20Jinping%20is%20also%20scheduled%20to%20attend%20the%20G-20%20summit%20in%20India%20in%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%2C%20even%20though%20there%20has%20been%20no%20official%20announcement%20so%20far.%20It%20would%20b