ity%20of%20time%20and%20space%3B%20the%20cost%20of%20each%20solution%20at%20the%20time%20of%20implementation%20and%20over%20its%20lifetime%3B%20the%20skill%20required%20to%20maintain%20the%20solution%3B%20and%20the%20potential%20incidental%20benefits%20worthy%20of%20investments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUrban%20forests%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20require%20at%20least%20three%20years%20of%20care%20before%20the%20trees%20are%20fully%20grown%20and%20the%20spaces%20become%20self-sustaining%20ecosystems.%20The%20selection%20of%20trees%2C%20too%2C%20must%20consider%20the%20appropriate%20native%20species%2C%20the%20urban%20context%20such%20as%20the%20availability%20of%20water%2C%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20overhead%20and%20underground%20cables%20and%20drains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20shed%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20can%20be%20constructed%20quickly%20and%20can%20provide%20shade.%20However%2C%20it%20will%20lack%20the%20co-benefits%20of%20managing%20rainfall%20and%20providing%20a%20habitat%20to%20the%20local%20biodiversity%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20aesthetic%20appeal%20of%20a%20tree.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20competition%20over%20space%20and%20resources%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20choose%20between%20a%20nature-based%20solution%20or%20grey%20infrastructure%2C%20but%20instead%20it%20must%20see%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwri-india.org%2Fblog%2Fliving-water-integrating-blue-green-and-grey-infrastructure-manage-urban-floods%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20well%20both%20can%20be%20integrated%20to%20shape%20more%20resilient%20cities.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-forest-1693381917.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.th