%3EThe%20scammers%20send%20a%20text%20message%20to%20your%20phone%20that%20closely%20remembers%20e-challan%20alerts.%20The%20messages%20have%20a%20payment%20link.%20One%20you%20click%20on%20it%2C%20your%20phone's%20security%20is%20compromised%2C%20and%20the%20hackers%20get%20access%20to%20your%20credit%2Fdebit%20card%20details.%20Before%20you%20know%2C%20you%20have%20been%20conned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20To%20Avoid%20Getting%20Conned%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20police%2C%20scammers%20have%20meticulously%20copied%20the%20format%20used%20by%20traffic%20authorities.%20However%2C%20a%20close%20examination%20can%20help%20us%20spot%20the%20trap.%20The%20payment%20link%20in%20e-challans%20is%20https%3A%2F%2Fechallan.parivahan.gov.in%2F.%20The%20scammers%20use%20links%20that%20read%20very%20similar%2C%20and%20a%20casual%20glance%20can%20miss%20the%20difference.%20https%3A%2F%2Fechallan.parivahan.in%2F%20is%20an%20example.%20An%20actual%20e-challan%20payment%20link%20will%20end%20with%20%26quot%3Bgov.in%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20Ways%20To%20Spot%20The%20Scam%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20critical%20that%20you%20do%20not%20make%20such%20payments%20in%20a%20haste.%20According%20to%20senior%20cyber%20police%20officers%2C%20vehicle%20owners%20must%20check%20such%20messages%20carefully%20before%20clicking%20on%20any%20link.%20A%20key%20way%20to%20identify%20real%20messages%20is%20that%20they%20will%20have%20details%20of%20your%20vehicle%2C%20its%20engine%20number%20and%20chassis%20number.%20Such%20information%20will%20not%20be%20on%20SMS%20traps%20sent%20by%20scammers.%20Another%20precaution%20could%20be%20to%20visit%20the%20official%20government%20website%20to%20check%20if%20you%20have%20actually%20been%20fined.%20Also%2C%20an%20e-challan%20alert%20will%20never%20come%20from%20a%20cellphone%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20To%20Do%20If%20You%20Are%20Conned%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3