ent%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20China.%20The%20trip%20aims%20to%20improve%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20which%20have%20been%20strained%20due%20to%20concerns%20over%20security%2C%20investment%2C%20and%20human%20rights.%20Cleverly%20argued%20against%20isolating%20China%20and%20stressed%20the%20need%20for%20collaboration%20on%20global%20issues%20like%20climate%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fuk-clear-eyed-about-disagreements-with-china-says-british-foreign-secretary%2Farticleshow%2F103202571.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fuk-clear-eyed-about-disagreements-with-china-says-british-foreign-secretary%2Famp_articleshow%2F103202571.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fuk-clear-eyed-about-disagreements-with-china-says-british-foreign-secretary%2Famp_articleshow%2F103202571.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20Laws%20Create%20Dangerous%20'Backdoor'%20for%20Surveillance%20Companies%2C%20Govt%20Surveillance%3A%20FT%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F21193814%2Fsurveillance.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cso-called%20lawful%20interception%20monitoring%20systems%E2%80%9D%20are%20helping%20provide%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbackdoor%E2%80%9D%20that%20allows%20%E2%80%9Cprime%20minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20government%20to%20snoop%20on%20its%201.4bn%20citizens%2C%20part%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20growing%20surveillance%20regime%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fadf1cbae-4217-4d7d-9271-8bec41a56fb4%5C%22%3Ereports%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prestigious%20London-based%20financial%20daily%20tracks%20how%20India%20mandates%20that%20telecommunication%20networks%20install%20hardware%20%E2%80%9Cto%20search%2C%20copy%20and%20pump%20that%20data%20to%20Indian%20security%20agencies%20on%20demand%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20AI%20and%20data%20analytics%E2%80%9D.%20This%20hardware%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20attached%20to%20%E2%80%9Csubsea%20cable%20landing%20stations%20that%20have%20proliferated%20around%20India%E2%80%99s%20coast.%E2%80%9D%20It%20is%20these%20cables%20that%20make%20global%20communications%20between%20India%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20possible%20in%20the%20digital%20age.%20This%2C%20it%20finds%2C%20is%20fuelling%20and%20helping%20private%20companies%20that%20sell%20powerful%20surveillance%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20FT%20identifies%20include%20Indian%20providers%20such%20as%20Vehere%2C%20%E2%80%9Cas%20well%20as%20less%20well%20known%20Israeli%20groups%20like%20Cognyte%20or%20Septier.%E2%80%9D%20The%20profile%20and%20track-record%20of%20some%20of%20these%20companies%20have%20raised%20serious%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeptier%20was%20among%20companies%20termed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpotentially%20irresponsible%20proliferator%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%20in%202021%2C%20which%20it%20meant%20as%20those%20companies%20%E2%80%9Cwilling%20to%20accept%20or%20ignore%20the%20risk%20that%20their%20products%20will%20bolster%20the%20capabilities%20of%20client%20governments%20that%20might%20wish%20to%20threaten%20US%2FNato%20national%20security%20or%20harm%20marginalised%20populations%E2%80%9D.%20Septier%20called%20this%20%E2%80%9Cpure%20speculation%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20time%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20case%20is%20unusual%20and%20an%20exception%20to%20most%20other%20democracies%2C%20as%20it%20requires%20%E2%80%9Ctelecom%20companies%20to%20install%20surveillance%20equipment%20at%20subsea%20cable%20landing%20stations%20and%20data%20centres%20that%20is%20approved%20by%20the%20government%20as%20a%20condition%20of%20operation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Snowden%20tapes%20created%20a%20storm%2C%20revealing%20how%20intelligence%20agencies%20in%20the%20US%20and%20UK%20were%20engaged%20in%20mass%20surveillance%20via%20backdoor%20arrangements%2C%20telecom%20companies%20have%20pushed%20back%20on%20government%20pressure%20%E2%80%9Cto%20install%20official%20backdoors%20providing%20unfettered%20access%20to%20customer%20data.%E2%80%9D%20They%20have%20preferred%20to%20demand%20a%20court-approved%20warrant%20for%20targeted%20interception%2C%20as%20and%20when%20governments%20have%20made%20requests%20for%20surveillance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20finds%20itself%20amongst%20countries%20like%20Uganda%20and%20Rwanda%2C%20who%20have%20similar%20interception%20laws.%20But%2C%20remarks%20FT%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20telecoms%20usage%20has%20zoomed%20in%20recent%20years.%20Projections%20of%20wireless%20data%20usage%20are%20up%20%E2%80%9Cfrom%20an%20average%20of%201.24GB%20per%20person%20a%20month%20in%202018%20to%20over%2014GB.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20companies%20we%20keep%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeptier%20is%20an%20Israel-based%20company.%20Founded%20in%202000%2C%20has%20sold%20its%20lawful%20interception%20technology%20to%20telecoms%20groups%20including%20Mukesh%20Ambani%E2%80%99s%20Reliance%20Jio%2C%20the%20Vodafone%20Idea%20Indian%20joint%20venture%20and%20Singapore%E2%80%99s%20Singtel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael-based%20Cognyte%2C%20is%20cited%20as%20another%20leading%20provider%20of%20surveillance%20products%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVehere%2C%20jointly%20headquartered%20in%20India%20and%20the%20US%2C%20is%20also%20mentioned%20as%20a%20company%20relevant%20in%20this%20context.%20It%20advertises%20its%20%E2%80%9Cstate%20of%20the%20art%20monitoring%20solution%E2%80%9D%20that%20helps%20telecom%20companies%20%E2%80%9Cfulfil%20their%20legal%20obligation%20to%20intercept%20calls%20and%20data%20while%20maintaining%20maximum%20privacy%20protection%E2%80%9D%2C%20says%20FT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20contacted%20the%20government%20of%20India%2C%20Cognyte%2C%20Vehere%2C%20Reliance%20Jio%20and%20Singtel%20for%20comments%2C%20but%20says%20they%20did%20not%20respond.%20Vodafone%20Idea%20said%20it%20%E2%80%9Cremains%20strictly%20compliant%20to%20licensing%20conditions%20mandated%20by%20%5Bthe%5D%20government%20of%20India%20and%20the%20prevailing%20regulations%20in%20force%20at%20any%20given%20time%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBroader%20concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConcerns%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20surveillance%20regime%20have%20multiplied%20since%20reports%20about%20India%20deploying%20the%20Pegasus%20spyware%20of%20Israeli%20group%20NSO%2C%20%E2%80%9Ctriggering%20a%20political%20scandal%20when%20the%20hacking%20tool%20was%20found%20on%20the%20phones%20of%20journalists%20and%20activists%20in%202019%20and%202021.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202021%2C%2016%20international%20news%20organisations%20including%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20French%20media%20non-profit%20Forbidden%20Stories%20and%20Amnesty%20International%20c%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Frevealed-how-the-wire-partners-cracked-pegasus-project-implications-india%5C%22%3Eame%20together%20to%20expose%20the%20use%20of%20this%20spyware%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20the%20NSO%20Group%20said%20it%20only%20sold%20to%20governments%20%E2%80%93%20was%20used%20across%20the%20world%2C%20including%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20personal%20data%20protection%20bill%20passed%20in%20this%20monsoon%20session%20of%20Parliament%20has%20been%20criticised%20for%20being%20one%20that%20protects%20governments%20from%20scrutiny%20and%20not%20citizens%2C%20providing%20legal%20cover%20for%20surveillance.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-lies-beneath-the-pr-blitz-on-the-new-data-protection-act%5C%22%3ECritics%20and%20activists%20say%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20government%E2%80%99s%20favourite%20catchphrase%20%E2%80%98as%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%99%20is%20the%20highlight%20of%20this%20DPDP%20Act.%20It%20has%20been%20used%2028%20times%20in%20a%2021-page%20Act%20with%2044%20sections.%20The%20ambiguity%20has%20been%20kept%20so%20that%20the%20government%20can%20take%20arbitrary%20decisions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693380610000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F21193814%2Fsurveillance.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findias-laws-create-dangerous-backdoor-for-surveillance-companies-govt-surveillance-ft%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20finds%20itself%20amongst%20countries%20like%20Uganda%20and%20Rwanda%2C%20as%20far%20as%20laws%20allowing%20for%20interception%20of%20communication%20goes.%20Most%20companies%20globally%20ask%20governments%20for%20a%20%E2%80%98court-approved%20warrant%20for%20targeted%20interception%E2%80%99.%20Not%20so%2C%20here.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findias-laws-create-dangerous-backdoor-for-surveillance-companies-govt-surveillance-ft%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Former%20Pakistan%20PM%20Imran%20Khan's%20judicial%20remand%20extended%20till%20Sep%2013%20in%20cipher%20case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693379748000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103202034%2Cimgsize-22654.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fformer-pakistan-pm-imran-khans-judicial-remand-extended-till-sep-13-in-cipher-case%2Farticleshow%2F103201878.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103201878.cms%5C