%20listed%20in%20order%20of%20their%20weight%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20ingredient%20is%20the%20one%20the%20packet%20contains%20the%20most.%20So%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20buying%20biscuits%2C%20the%20first%20three%20ingredients%20usually%20will%20be%20maida%20(refined%20wheat%20flour)%2C%20palm%20oil%20and%20sugar%E2%80%9D%20says%20Revant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuy%20items%20that%20have%20less%20than%20five%20ingredients%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTry%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20products%20that%20have%20more%20than%20five%20ingredients.%20As%20the%20ingredient%20list%20increases%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20inversely%20proportional%20to%20the%20nutritional%20benefits.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAvoid%20products%20that%20have%20complicated%20ingredients%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20recognise%20or%20pronounce%20ingredients%20in%20a%20product%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20good%20for%20you.%20Buy%20the%20product%20in%20which%20you%20can%20understand%20the%20ingredient%2C%20like%20something%20that%20says%20dates%2C%20peanuts%2C%20milk%2C%20etc.%20If%20something%20has%20ingredients%20like%20maltodextrin%2C%20anti-caking%20agent%2C%20technical%20chemicals%2C%20stay%20away%20from%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%224%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuy%20items%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20list%20sugar%20in%20the%20first%205-6%20ingredients%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSteer%20clear%20of%20products%20that%20have%20sugar%20listed%20first%20or%20second.%20Those%20products%20are%20basically%20just%20sugar.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%225%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGo%20for%20the%20slightly%20healthier%20options%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20whole%20idea%20is%20to%20make%20healthier%20choices.%20Instead%20of%20going%20for%20a%20%3Cem%3Emaida%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebiscuit%2C%20go%20for%20an%20%3Cem%3Eatta%20%3C%2Fem%3E(whole%20wheat%20flour)%20biscuit.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%226%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20best%20food%20for%20you%20is%20one%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20label%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUltimately%2C%20the%20healthiest%20foods%20are%20the%20ones%20without%20any%20labels%2C%20fruits%20and%20vegetables.%20If%20you%20must%20buy%20other%20products%2C%20go%20for%20simple%20products%20that%20have%20ingredients%20you%20know.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20buying%20peanut%20butter%2C%20go%20for%20products%20which%20just%20have%20peanuts%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Revant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20quest%20to%20make%20the%20next%20generation%20healthier%20and%20wiser%20about%20their%20food%20choices%2C%20Revant%20dreams%20of%20a%20day%20when%20every%20child%20is%20taught%20how%20to%20read%20food%20labels.%20He%20now%20goes%20to%20schools%20and%20colleges%20to%20teach%20students%20this%20skill%20as%20well.%20Here%2C%20he%20often%20finds%20that%20children%20ask%20interesting%20and%20intelligent%20questions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20question%20why%20the%20front%20of%20the%20packets%20say%20something%20that%20the%20product%20clearly%20does%20not%20do.%20They%20want%20to%20know%20why%20their%20favourite%20celebrity%20is%20endorsing%20a%20product%20which%20is%20unhealthy.%20I%20am%20hopeful%20that%20this%20will%20lead%20to%20better%20choices%2C%E2%80%9D%20smiles%20Revant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20children%20are%20taught%20how%20to%20read%20a%20food%20label%20and%20understand%20the%20consequences%2C%20it%20will%20bring%20about%20a%20massive%20change.%20Companies%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20market%20themselves%20honestly%2C%20and%20this%20will%20change%20the%20game.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%20and%20Divya%20Sethu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESources%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unicef.org%2Freports%2Fstate-of-worlds-children-2019%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUNICEF%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692353848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FRevant-1692350285.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D327558%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Revant%20Himatsingka%2C%20aka%20foodpharmer%20on%20Instagram%2C%20terms%20reading%20food%20labels%20the%20most%20important%20life%20skill.%20His%20aim%20is%20to%20expose%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20marketing%E2%80%9D%20by%20FMCGs%20and%20educate%20people%20on%20what%20they%20are%20truly%20consuming.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F327558%2Frevant-himatsingka-foodpharmer-shares-how-to-read-food-labels-for-health-risks%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Engineer%E2%80%99s%20Low-Cost%20Model%20Helps%208000%20Farmers%20Cut%2099%25%20Water%20Use%2C%20Harvest%20500%20KG%20Fodder%2FDay%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20time%20as%20a%20sales%20engineer%20in%20Dubai%2C%20Ashwin%20Sawant%20met%20a%20client%20who%20was%20cultivating%20green%20fodder%20hydroponically%20for%20his%20large%20livestock%2C%20consisting%20of%20over%202%2C000%20animals.%20This%20farm%20left%20such%20an%20impression%20on%20him%20that%20he%20chose%20to%20leave%20his%20lucrative%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20never%20seen%20such%20an%20impressive%20setup%20before%2C%20so%20I%20started%20frequenting%20the%20client.%20Observing%20their%20work%20helped%20me%20gain%20the%20confidence%20to%20replicate%20something%20similar.%20Lately%2C%20I%20had%20not%20been%20happy%20with%20my%20work%20in%20Dubai%20and%20was%20looking%20for%20a%20reason%20to%20come%20back%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%2038-year-old%20Mumbai%20resident%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidering%20hydroponics%20to%20be%20his%20calling%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20his%20grandparent%E2%80%99s%20village%20in%20Pune%20in%202011.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20concept%20of%20hydroponics%20was%20very%20new%20back%20then.%20People%20would%20find%20it%20hard%20even%20to%20pronounce%20it%20%E2%80%94%20some%20would%20term%20it%20hydrophobic%20and%20%E2%80%98hydrolonic%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-3-1692278469.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ashwin%20harvests%20500%20kilos%20of%20green%20fodder%20daily%20to%20feed%20the%20105%20cows%20and%20goats%20on%20his%20farm.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-3-1692278469.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-3-1692278469-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-3-1692278469-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-3-1692278469-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-3-1692278469-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-327491%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAshwin%20harvests%20500%20kilos%20of%20green%20fodder%20daily%20to%20feed%20the%20105%20cows%20and%20goats%20on%20his%20farm.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20any%20farming%20background%2C%20Ashwin%20started%20to%20grow%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F258493%2Fengineer-solar-powered-hydroponic-growing-unit-automated-fodder-production-energy-efficient-farmers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreen%20fodder%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20the%20500%20sq%20ft%20of%20land%20in%20Pune.%20Today%2C%20he%20harvests%20500%20kilos%20of%20green%20fodder%20daily%20to%20feed%20the%20105%20cows%20and%20goats%20on%20his%20farm.%20He%20also%20set%20up%20a%20research%20lab%20%E2%80%98Scientific%20Hydroponics%E2%80%99%20to%20introduce%20farmers%20to%20the%20benefits%20of%20hydroponics%20farming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EChanging%20the%20game%20for%20Indian%20farmers%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshwin%20points%20out%20that%20Indian%20farmers%20lack%20access%20to%20green%20fodder%20because%20it%20requires%20large%20tracts%20of%20land%20and%20gallons%20of%20water.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20states%20like%20Haryana%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20farmers%20already%20lack%20sufficient%20water%20for%20irrigation.%20If%20a%20farmer%20owns%20800%20cows%2C%20they%20have%20to%20reserve%2060%20acres%20of%20land%20to%20grow%20green%20fodder.%20That%20means%20they%20cannot%20grow%20any%20other%20crop%20on%20this%20land%2C%20which%20is%20not%20economical%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20with%20hydroponics%2C%20we%20can%20reduce%20the%20area%20and%20water%20requirements.%20With%20a%20one-tonne%20unit%20that%20can%20be%20installed%20in%20a%201%2C000-sq%20ft%20area%2C%20a%20farmer%20can%20save%20at%20least%20seven%20acres%20of%20land.%20This%20land%20can%20be%20utilised%20to%20grow%20other%20crops.%20Using%20hydroponics%2C%20farmers%20can%20harvest%20one%20kilo%20of%20green%20fodder%20by%20utilising%20just%201.5%20litres%20of%20water%20while%20saving%2099%20percent%20of%20the%20water%20required%20conventionally%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-1-1692278339.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ashwin%20helps%20farmers%20grow%20green%20fodder%20like%20maize%2C%20barley%2C%20wheat%20for%20goats%2C%20cows%2C%20buffaloes%2C%20ducks.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-1-1692278339.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-1-1692278339-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-1-1692278339-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-1-1692278339-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fashwin-sawant-1-1692278339-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-327487%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAshwin%20helps%20farmers%20grow%20green%20fodder%20like%20maize%2C%20barley%2C%20and%20wheat%20for%20goats%2C%20cows%2C%20buffaloes%2C%20and%20ducks.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20this%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20green%20fodder%20is%20an%20added%20woe.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20a%20farmer%20does%20not%20have%20enough%20land%20to%20grow%20green%20fodder%20on%20their%20own%2C%20they%20are%20forced%20to%20purchase%20expensive%20fodder%20from%20the%20market.%20The%20green%20fodder%20grown%20using%20traditional%20methods%20costs%20Rs%208%E2%80%9314%20per%20kg%20whereas%20that%20grown%20hydroponically%20costs%20Rs%202%20per%20kg%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20benefits%20of%20conserving%20land%20and%20water%2C%20the%20main%20drawback%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F265317%2Futtar-pradesh-hydroponics-farm-home-grows-vegetables-fruits-earns-lakhs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehydroponic%20technique%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20its%20expensive%20cost.%20Aswhin%20says%20a%20one-tonne%20unit%20costs%20up%20to%20Rs%2016%20lakh.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20setups%20require%20air%20conditioners%2C%20ozonators%2C%20and%20UV%20and%20RO%20systems.%20This%20increases%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20unit.%20I%20wanted%20to%20reduce%20its%20price%20so%20that%20many%20farmers%20can%20adopt%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20multiple%20trials%20and%20errors%2C%20Ashwin%20developed%20a%20low-cost%20economical%20model%20that%20cost%20Rs%203%20lakh%20on%20average.%20This%20model%20could%20be%20replicated%20across%20various%20geographies%20in%20the%20country.%20Ashwin%20worked%20on%20vital%20parameters%20like%20temperature%20and%20humidity%20required%20to%20promote%20the%20growth%20of%20green%20fodder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20regulate%20temperature%2C%20he%20replaced%20air%20conditioners%20with%20his%20%E2%80%98fan-and-pad%E2%80%99%20based%20cooling%20system%20that%20uses%20exhaust%20fans%20to%20pull%20air%20through%20cooling%20pads%2C%20which%20then%20evaporate%20water%20to%20cool%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20summer%2C%20the%20temperature%20shoots%20up%20to%2042%20degrees%20Celsius.%20To%20grow%20fodder%20like%20maize%2C%20you%20require%20a%20temperature%20of%2028%E2%80%9330%20degrees%20Celsius%3B%20whereas%20for%20wheat%20or%20barley%2C%20the%20temperature%20should%20be%2020-24%20degrees%20Celsius.%20This%20fan-and-pad%20system%20reduces%20the%20temperature%20to%20up%20to%2020%20degrees%20Celsius.%20It%20is%20designed%20like%20a%20cooler%20but%20works%20like%20an%20AC%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D